  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Resident Technical Officer # C&S Jurong Island",
  "description": "<h2>Resident Technical Officer # C&S Jurong Island<br />\nAbout the role</h2><ul><li>Site-based supervision of  all C&S works for the substation project at Tembusu Crescent, Jurong\nIsland, ensuring structural integrity and constructability.​</li><li>Full-time position on a 2‑year project.</li></ul><p><strong>Key responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Supervise and coordinate C&S construction activities to ensure compliance with approved\ndrawings, specifications, regulatory requirements, and safety standards.​</li><li>Monitor contractors’ work progress, identify and resolve site issues promptly, and provide technical\nguidance to the project team and stakeholders.​</li><li>Review and verify shop drawings, method statements and material submissions; prepare site reports\nand support inspections, testing and audits.​</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum Diploma or Bachelor’s degree in Civil / Structural Engineering or a\nconstruction-related discipline, meeting IES/ACES RTO registration criteria.​</li><li>At least 8 years of relevant experience in C&S site supervision for building or infrastructure\nprojects, preferably in substation or industrial developments.​</li><li>Registered with IES as a C&S RTO; safety-related certifications (e.g. BCSS or equivalent) will be\nan advantage.​</li><li>Strong communication skills, proactive attitude and ability to work effectively with consultants,\ncontractors and authorities in a team environment.</li></ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 8,
